reviewText: Rob Cohen delivers a competent and satisfying action film. The story, which incorporates well executed rationale action scenes, is easy to follow and fun. Considering that this movie was made for TV, the level of action is surprising. Unlike so many made for TV movies which only have one real chase scene, this movie has several throughout the film's plot.  This movie does not have the over the top special effects held in such high regard in the Fast and Furious franchise, but instead has well executed practical effects which create more believable action. Because the driving sequences look believable this movie gains a level of sophistication that classic car films understood. This is a film that may not have successfully launched a rebirth of the GTO, but instead should stand as a great car film.

reviewText: ... is that it has a '69 Judge in it. The movie was made to promote the new GTO when it originally came out in 2004, so the show is basically a big ad for Pontiac. Lot of good that did for the GTO or the company. Hopper does ok ... he obviously didn't put much heart or effort into his role. But then, the story was pretty predictable and lame. There are a few fun driving scenes to watch. If you're a car guy, it's worth owning ... if you can get it cheap enough. I happen to own a '69 Judge, so it was sort of a must-have for me because of that (along with Sex Drive ... which, frankly, was better than this). If nothing else, car guys will have fun laughing at it, and that alone probably makes it worth getting -- especially if you watch it with some buddies.

reviewText: This is a movie for people who love cars, period.  It's no masterpiece or massive Hollywood bonanza, but a good addition to any car fan's collection, and delivers a generous dose of action - expected from this genre of car/action movies.Well produced and well executed and creative in places.  It's almost like a Pontiac commercial in some spots, but redeems itself with interesting characters and great acting from Dennis Hopper, who adds his own "gravitas" to this title.  Also, true car nuts will appreciate the scene with the car show - I know I did since I go to them every year...!For the first 20 minutes or so its pure Boy Racer meets Old Hot Rodder criminal (or Easy Rider?) - but with a twist.  "JJ" (Carmack's girlfriend) is easy on the eyes, for sure.If you are a fan of Hopper, or a fan of Fast and Furious (this movie was produced by the same guy), then this movie is a nice gem you might have missed.Originally aired on cable on USA Network, the DVD has a lot of extras and the pleasant straight run with no commercials.Interviews director and the castBehind the scenesGTO Test DriveGTO Historical Video2005 Pontiac GTO Preview
summary: Great Movie for Car Addicts - Dennis Hopper is Back!
